~ start
if GameManager.get_current_level_flag("mcbucket_zanopram_used") == true:
	=> drugged_branch

# Set the background
do change_background("sergey_background", "fade", 0.5)

# Bring Sergey onto the stage
do actor_show("Sergey", "base", "center")

A man in his mid-forties sits upright on his bed.
His sharp eyes track you as you stir. He looks Slavic.

do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
Sergey: Ah. You wake. Good. Was not sure you ever would.
do SoundManager.play_music_track("sergey_sad_theme", 5.0)

~ hub
do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
Sergey: So then… tell me. How can Sergey help?

- How long was I out?
	set ConversationEventManager.asked_sergey_duration = true
	do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
	Sergey: Hard to say. You sleep long time. Since I arrive here, you do not move. Like statue. 
	- I can't recall anything.
		do actor_change("Sergey", "frown")
		Sergey: Hm. That is… not good. 
		Sergey: You truly remember nothing?
		- Nope. Nothing at all.
			do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
			Sergey: Then maybe this is fresh start, da? Clean page.
			
			do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
			Sergey: In Russia we say… sometimes forgetting is gift.
			
			do actor_change("Sergey", "eyes_closed")
			He gives a small shrug, as if to brush off the heaviness of his words.
			set ConversationEventManager.has_heard_fresh_start_line = true 
			=> hub

- Who are you?
	set ConversationEventManager.asked_sergey_identity = true
	do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
	Sergey: Name is Sergey. Heart had attack, so now I sit here.
	Sergey: Happen right before I was about to leave the country, too. Bad timing.  
	- Leaving? Where to?
		do actor_change("Sergey", "eyes_closed")
		Sergey: Home. Russia.
		Sergey: Before this, I was research contractor for HAVEMORE Defense.
		
		do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
		Sergey: Not soldier - I worked with machines. Autonomous systems… behavior models… things that are supposed to make security “more efficient”.
		
		do actor_change("Sergey", "eyes_closed")
		He gives a small, humorless laugh.
		Sergey: Is funny. Work was not dangerous, but somehow… still hurts the head. The heart too, maybe.
		- Stressful job?
			do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
			Sergey: Hm. Stressful… yes. Very quiet type of stress.
			
			do actor_change("Sergey", "frown")
			Sergey: Too many screens. Too many decisions that are not really decisions.
			Sergey: People there burn out without fire.
			
			He shifts under the blanket, adjusting his position.
			do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_behind_head")
			Sergey: Anyway… I told my manager I bring resignation letter next day.
			
			do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
			Sergey: Felt lighter than I had in years. Finally, I could go home, see snow, maybe drink tea with my little sister.
			
			He taps his chest lightly.
			Sergey: That night-boom. Heart decides to protest.
			Sergey: HAVEMORE doctors saved me, da. But their insurance only works if I am still employee.
			Sergey: If I quit now… bills will finish me faster than heart ever tried.
			
			do actor_change("Sergey", "eyes_closed")
			He gives a small shrug, resigned but not bitter.
			
			do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
			Sergey: So I stay. At least until I can stand without that Nurse Bot helping me up.
			- I'm so sorry to hear that.
				do actor_change("Sergey", "base")
				Sergey: Eh. No need for sorry.
				
				do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
				Sergey: Life is… how you say… stubborn. It goes where it wants.
				
				do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
				Sergey: I just follow for now.
				Sergey: But enough about Sergey.
				Sergey: What about you, hm? 
				
				if ConversationEventManager.has_heard_fresh_start_line == true:
					do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_behind_head")
					Sergey: Oh wait. Just remember. No memories, da? Sorry. 
					=> hub
				else:
					He wants to know about your background
					- I can't recall anything.
						do actor_change("Sergey", "frown")
						set ConversationEventManager.has_heard_fresh_start_line = true 
						Sergey: Really? that is not good.
						Sergey: Did the Nurse tell you anything?
						- They said I am here because of a drug overdose.
							do actor_change("Sergey", "frown_look_away")
							Sergey: Boze Moy. Sergey is sorry about that.
							Sergey: Hope you find peace in your new life. 
							=> hub

- How can I use the MemoryBox ™? [Proceed] [if GameManager.get_current_level_flag("has_spoken_to_aida") and GameManager.get_current_level_flag("has_tried_memory_box") and ConversationEventManager.asked_sergey_duration and ConversationEventManager.asked_sergey_identity]
	do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
	Sergey: That machine? Simple. Just put in your TechPass™, turn the machine on, and put your hand on the scanner. Boom, you can access your memories.

	do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
	Sergey: I tried once. Helps if you feel lost or..

	do show_cg("sergey_closeup_lookaway_sad")
	Sergey: ..Lonely.

	do hide_cg()
	#He pauses, then shakes his head.
	do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_behind_head")
	Sergey: But I do not look backward anymore. Only forward.
