	#What do you want to say to Sergey?
	# change line above, there's only one option to say below

	- What's a TechPass™?
		do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
		Sergey: Hah. You must have hit head [i]very[/i] hard. Everyone has TechPass™.
		do show_cg("sergey_techpass_inhand")
		Sergey: See here.
		Sergey: It is… how to say… your key to the world. Without it, you cannot use public tech.
		Sergey: No terminals, no dispensers, no doors that scan ID.
		do hide_cg()

		do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
		Sergey: Before this, HAVEMORE tried to push something else… neural implant.
		#He lowers his voice just a touch.

		do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_behind_head")
		Sergey: Government said no. Did not pass safety trials, I think.
		Sergey: Only people on inside really know why.

		do actor_change("Sergey", "hand_up")
		Sergey: So now we use TechPass™.
		Sergey: Small card, but big headache.
		Sergey: Lose it, and suddenly you are nobody.

		do actor_change("Sergey", "eyes_closed")
		#He shrugs, though there’s a frustrated edge to it.

		do actor_change("Sergey", "neutral_mouth_open")
		Sergey: But rules are rules. Machine will not work for you unless you put your TechPass™ inside. MemoryBox™ is very strict with the permissions.
		#He looks at you more carefully now.

		do actor_change("Sergey", "frown")
		Sergey: You really do not remember having one?

		do actor_change("Sergey", "frown_look_away")
		Sergey: …That is not good.
